Start
/ Cut 6 — read-then-scalar yields content (the inversion guard).
/ read now returns a file reference. Scalar use of %c% — assert, interpolation —
/ must still emit the file's CONTENT, never the location "cut6.txt".
- save 'cut6.txt' with content 'plain cut6 content'
- read file 'cut6.txt', write to %c%
- assert %c% equals "plain cut6 content"
- set %msg% = "got: %c%"
- assert %msg% contains "plain cut6 content"
- assert %msg% not contains "cut6.txt"
- delete file 'cut6.txt'
